BasicIO

Class ASCIIOutputFile

  • java.lang.Object
    • BasicIO.ASCIIOutputFile

  • public class ASCIIOutputFile
extends java.lang.Object
    ASCIIOutputFile writes unformated text to a file suitable to be read by ASCIIDataFile. This text is broken into fields delimited by tabs and newline (End of Line) characters. Tabs are automatically inserted between fields on all write operations with the exception of writeLine and writeC. writeLine writes a newline character after writing the String parameter passed to it. writeC will write the character without field separators. Its purpose is for raw data output. If you wish to write a single char to a field use writeChar. If the data cannot be written to the file, either due to lack of space, or the file cannot be found, then the successful method will return false.
    Version:
    1.0 July 08, 2.0 (09/06/30)
    Author:
    A. Cheesman, David Hughes
